'From Squeak2.9alpha of 13 June 2000 [latest update: #2856] on 10 October 2000 at 10:39:29 pm'!"Change Set:		RetractModalShellDate:			10 October 2000Author:			Andreas RaabRetracts the entire damn thing. It was a bad idea."!!FillInTheBlankMorph methodsFor: 'initialization' stamp: 'ar 10/10/2000 22:35'!delete	self breakDependents.	super delete.! !!FillInTheBlankMorph methodsFor: 'invoking' stamp: 'ar 10/10/2000 22:37'!getUserResponse	"Wait for the user to accept or cancel, and answer the result string. Answers the empty string if the user cancels."	"Details: This is invoked synchronously from the caller. In order to keep processing inputs and updating the screen while waiting for the user to respond, this method has its own version of the World's event loop."	| w |	w _ self world.	w ifNil: [^ response].	done _ false.	[done] whileFalse: [Display doOneCycleMorphic].	self delete.	Display doOneCycleMorphic.	^ response! !FillInTheBlankMorph removeSelector: #aboutToBeGrabbedBy:!FillInTheBlankMorph removeSelector: #addModalShell!FillInTheBlankMorph removeSelector: #justDroppedInto:event:!Smalltalk removeClassNamed: #ModalShellMorph!